{"id":835971412,"question_id":264,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 year, 7 months","timestamp":1667468841,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"3 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/835971412/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Ugly Number II","memory":"40.5 MB","code":"class Solution {\n   public int nthUglyNumber(int n) {\n       int idx2=0, idx3=0, idx5=0;\n       \n       int[] dp = new int[n+1];\n       dp[0]=1;\n       \n       for(int i=1; i<n; i++){\n           dp[i] = Math.min(dp[idx2]*2, Math.min(dp[idx3]*3, dp[idx5]*5));\n           \n           if(dp[i]==dp[idx2]*2)\n               idx2++;\n           \n           if(dp[i]==dp[idx3]*3)\n               idx3++;\n           \n           if(dp[i]==dp[idx5]*5)\n               idx5++;\n           \n           // System.out.println(dp[i]);\n       }\n       return dp[n-1];\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"ugly-number-ii","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
